2781// format_dragon flags.
2782enum dragon {
2783 predecessor_closer = 1,
2784 fixup = 2, // Run fixup to correct exp10 which can be off by one.
2785 fixed = 4,
2786};
2787
2788// Formats a floating-point number using a variation of the Fixed-Precision
2789// Positive Floating-Point Printout ((FPP)^2) algorithm by Steele & White:
2790// https://fmt.dev/papers/p372-steele.pdf.
2791FMT_CONSTEXPR20 inline void format_dragon(basic_fp<uint128_t> value, unsigned flags, int num_digits, buffer<char>& buf,
2792 int& exp10) {
2793 bigint numerator; // 2 * R in (FPP)^2.
2794 bigint denominator; // 2 * S in (FPP)^2.
2795 // lower and upper are differences between value and corresponding boundaries.
2796 bigint lower; // (M^- in (FPP)^2).
2797 bigint upper_store; // upper's value if different from lower.
2798 bigint* upper = nullptr; // (M^+ in (FPP)^2).
2799 // Shift numerator and denominator by an extra bit or two (if lower boundary
2800 // is closer) to make lower and upper integers. This eliminates multiplication
2801 // by 2 during later computations.
2802 bool is_predecessor_closer = (flags & dragon::predecessor_closer) != 0;
2803 int shift = is_predecessor_closer ? 2 : 1;
2804 if (value.e >= 0) {
2805 numerator = value.f;
2806 numerator <<= value.e + shift;
2807 lower = 1;
2808 lower <<= value.e;
2809 if (is_predecessor_closer) {
2810 upper_store = 1;
2811 upper_store <<= value.e + 1;
2812 upper = &upper_store;
2813 }
2814 denominator.assign_pow10(exp10);
2815 denominator <<= shift;
2816 } else if (exp10 < 0) {
2817 numerator.assign_pow10(-exp10);
2818 lower.assign(numerator);
2819 if (is_predecessor_closer) {
2820 upper_store.assign(numerator);
2821 upper_store <<= 1;
2822 upper = &upper_store;
2823 }
2824 numerator *= value.f;
2825 numerator <<= shift;
2826 denominator = 1;
2827 denominator <<= shift - value.e;
2828 } else {
2829 numerator = value.f;
2830 numerator <<= shift;
2831 denominator.assign_pow10(exp10);
2832 denominator <<= shift - value.e;
2833 lower = 1;
2834 if (is_predecessor_closer) {
2835 upper_store = 1ULL << 1;
2836 upper = &upper_store;
2837 }
2838 }
2839 int even = static_cast<int>((value.f & 1) == 0);
2840 if (!upper) upper = &lower;
2841 bool shortest = num_digits < 0;
2842 if ((flags & dragon::fixup) != 0) {
2843 if (add_compare(numerator, *upper, denominator) + even <= 0) {
2844 --exp10;
2845 numerator *= 10;
2846 if (num_digits < 0) {
2847 lower *= 10;
2848 if (upper != &lower) *upper *= 10;
2849 }
2850 }
2851 if ((flags & dragon::fixed) != 0) adjust_precision(num_digits, exp10 + 1);
2852 }
2853 // Invariant: value == (numerator / denominator) * pow(10, exp10).
2854 if (shortest) {
2855 // Generate the shortest representation.
2856 num_digits = 0;
2857 char* data = buf.data();
2858 for (;;) {
2859 int digit = numerator.divmod_assign(denominator);
2860 bool low = compare(numerator, lower) - even < 0; // numerator <[=] lower.
2861 // numerator + upper >[=] pow10:
2862 bool high = add_compare(numerator, *upper, denominator) + even > 0;
2863 data[num_digits++] = static_cast<char>('0' + digit);
2864 if (low || high) {
2865 if (!low) {
2866 ++data[num_digits - 1];
2867 } else if (high) {
2868 int result = add_compare(numerator, numerator, denominator);
2869 // Round half to even.
2870 if (result > 0 || (result == 0 && (digit % 2) != 0)) ++data[num_digits - 1];
2871 }
2872 buf.try_resize(to_unsigned(num_digits));
2873 exp10 -= num_digits - 1;
2874 return;
2875 }
2876 numerator *= 10;
2877 lower *= 10;
2878 if (upper != &lower) *upper *= 10;
2879 }
2880 }
2881 // Generate the given number of digits.
2882 exp10 -= num_digits - 1;
2883 if (num_digits <= 0) {
2884 denominator *= 10;
2885 auto digit = add_compare(numerator, numerator, denominator) > 0 ? '1' : '0';
2886 buf.push_back(digit);
2887 return;
2888 }
2889 buf.try_resize(to_unsigned(num_digits));
2890 for (int i = 0; i < num_digits - 1; ++i) {
2891 int digit = numerator.divmod_assign(denominator);
2892 buf[i] = static_cast<char>('0' + digit);
2893 numerator *= 10;
2894 }
2895 int digit = numerator.divmod_assign(denominator);
2896 auto result = add_compare(numerator, numerator, denominator);
2897 if (result > 0 || (result == 0 && (digit % 2) != 0)) {
2898 if (digit == 9) {
2899 const auto overflow = '0' + 10;
2900 buf[num_digits - 1] = overflow;
2901 // Propagate the carry.
2902 for (int i = num_digits - 1; i > 0 && buf[i] == overflow; --i) {
2903 buf[i] = '0';
2904 ++buf[i - 1];
2905 }
2906 if (buf[0] == overflow) {
2907 buf[0] = '1';
2908 if ((flags & dragon::fixed) != 0) buf.push_back('0');
2909 else ++exp10;
2910 }
2911 return;
2912 }
2913 ++digit;
2914 }
2915 buf[num_digits - 1] = static_cast<char>('0' + digit);
2916}
2917
2918// Formats a floating-point number using the hexfloat format.
2919template <typename Float, FMT_ENABLE_IF(!is_double_double<Float>::value)>
2920FMT_CONSTEXPR20 void format_hexfloat(Float value, int precision, float_specs specs, buffer<char>& buf) {
2921 // float is passed as double to reduce the number of instantiations and to
2922 // simplify implementation.
2923 static_assert(!std::is_same<Float, float>::value, "");
2924
2925 using info = dragonbox::float_info<Float>;
2926
2927 // Assume Float is in the format [sign][exponent][significand].
2928 using carrier_uint = typename info::carrier_uint;
2929
2930 constexpr auto num_float_significand_bits = detail::num_significand_bits<Float>();
2931
2932 basic_fp<carrier_uint> f(value);
2933 f.e += num_float_significand_bits;
2934 if (!has_implicit_bit<Float>()) --f.e;
2935
2936 constexpr auto num_fraction_bits = num_float_significand_bits + (has_implicit_bit<Float>() ? 1 : 0);
2937 constexpr auto num_xdigits = (num_fraction_bits + 3) / 4;
2938
2939 constexpr auto leading_shift = ((num_xdigits - 1) * 4);
2940 const auto leading_mask = carrier_uint(0xF) << leading_shift;
2941 const auto leading_xdigit = static_cast<uint32_t>((f.f & leading_mask) >> leading_shift);
2942 if (leading_xdigit > 1) f.e -= (32 - countl_zero(leading_xdigit) - 1);
2943
2944 int print_xdigits = num_xdigits - 1;
2945 if (precision >= 0 && print_xdigits > precision) {
2946 const int shift = ((print_xdigits - precision - 1) * 4);
2947 const auto mask = carrier_uint(0xF) << shift;
2948 const auto v = static_cast<uint32_t>((f.f & mask) >> shift);
2949
2950 if (v >= 8) {
2951 const auto inc = carrier_uint(1) << (shift + 4);
2952 f.f += inc;
2953 f.f &= ~(inc - 1);
2954 }
2955
2956 // Check long double overflow
2957 if (!has_implicit_bit<Float>()) {
2958 const auto implicit_bit = carrier_uint(1) << num_float_significand_bits;
2959 if ((f.f & implicit_bit) == implicit_bit) {
2960 f.f >>= 4;
2961 f.e += 4;
2962 }
2963 }
2964
2965 print_xdigits = precision;
2966 }
2967
2968 char xdigits[num_bits<carrier_uint>() / 4];
2969 detail::fill_n(xdigits, sizeof(xdigits), '0');
2970 format_uint<4>(xdigits, f.f, num_xdigits, specs.upper);
2971
2972 // Remove zero tail
2973 while (print_xdigits > 0 && xdigits[print_xdigits] == '0') --print_xdigits;
2974
2975 buf.push_back('0');
2976 buf.push_back(specs.upper ? 'X' : 'x');
2977 buf.push_back(xdigits[0]);
2978 if (specs.showpoint || print_xdigits > 0 || print_xdigits < precision) buf.push_back('.');
2979 buf.append(xdigits + 1, xdigits + 1 + print_xdigits);
2980 for (; print_xdigits < precision; ++print_xdigits) buf.push_back('0');
2981
2982 buf.push_back(specs.upper ? 'P' : 'p');
2983
2984 uint32_t abs_e;
2985 if (f.e < 0) {
2986 buf.push_back('-');
2987 abs_e = static_cast<uint32_t>(-f.e);
2988 } else {
2989 buf.push_back('+');
2990 abs_e = static_cast<uint32_t>(f.e);
2991 }
2992 format_decimal<char>(appender(buf), abs_e, detail::count_digits(abs_e));
2993}
2994
2995template <typename Float, FMT_ENABLE_IF(is_double_double<Float>::value)>
2996FMT_CONSTEXPR20 void format_hexfloat(Float value, int precision, float_specs specs, buffer<char>& buf) {
2997 format_hexfloat(static_cast<double>(value), precision, specs, buf);
2998}
2999
3000template <typename Float>
3001FMT_CONSTEXPR20 auto format_float(Float value, int precision, float_specs specs, buffer<char>& buf) -> int {
3002 // float is passed as double to reduce the number of instantiations.
3003 static_assert(!std::is_same<Float, float>::value, "");
3004 FMT_ASSERT(value >= 0, "value is negative");
3005 auto converted_value = convert_float(value);
3006
3007 const bool fixed = specs.format == float_format::fixed;
3008 if (value <= 0) { // <= instead of == to silence a warning.
3009 if (precision <= 0 || !fixed) {
3010 buf.push_back('0');
3011 return 0;
3012 }
3013 buf.try_resize(to_unsigned(precision));
3014 fill_n(buf.data(), precision, '0');
3015 return -precision;
3016 }
3017
3018 int exp = 0;
3019 bool use_dragon = true;
3020 unsigned dragon_flags = 0;
3021 if (!is_fast_float<Float>() || is_constant_evaluated()) {
3022 const auto inv_log2_10 = 0.3010299956639812; // 1 / log2(10)
3023 using info = dragonbox::float_info<decltype(converted_value)>;
3024 const auto f = basic_fp<typename info::carrier_uint>(converted_value);
3025 // Compute exp, an approximate power of 10, such that
3026 // 10^(exp - 1) <= value < 10^exp or 10^exp <= value < 10^(exp + 1).
3027 // This is based on log10(value) == log2(value) / log2(10) and approximation
3028 // of log2(value) by e + num_fraction_bits idea from double-conversion.
3029 auto e = (f.e + count_digits<1>(f.f) - 1) * inv_log2_10 - 1e-10;
3030 exp = static_cast<int>(e);
3031 if (e > exp) ++exp; // Compute ceil.
3032 dragon_flags = dragon::fixup;
3033 } else if (precision < 0) {
3034 // Use Dragonbox for the shortest format.
3035 if (specs.binary32) {
3036 auto dec = dragonbox::to_decimal(static_cast<float>(value));
3037 write<char>(buffer_appender<char>(buf), dec.significand);
3038 return dec.exponent;
3039 }
3040 auto dec = dragonbox::to_decimal(static_cast<double>(value));
3041 write<char>(buffer_appender<char>(buf), dec.significand);
3042 return dec.exponent;
3043 } else {
3044 // Extract significand bits and exponent bits.
3045 using info = dragonbox::float_info<double>;
3046 auto br = bit_cast<uint64_t>(static_cast<double>(value));
3047
3048 const uint64_t significand_mask = (static_cast<uint64_t>(1) << num_significand_bits<double>()) - 1;
3049 uint64_t significand = (br & significand_mask);
3050 int exponent = static_cast<int>((br & exponent_mask<double>()) >> num_significand_bits<double>());
3051
3052 if (exponent != 0) { // Check if normal.
3053 exponent -= exponent_bias<double>() + num_significand_bits<double>();
3054 significand |= (static_cast<uint64_t>(1) << num_significand_bits<double>());
3055 significand <<= 1;
3056 } else {
3057 // Normalize subnormal inputs.
3058 FMT_ASSERT(significand != 0, "zeros should not appear here");
3059 int shift = countl_zero(significand);
3060 FMT_ASSERT(shift >= num_bits<uint64_t>() - num_significand_bits<double>(), "");
3061 shift -= (num_bits<uint64_t>() - num_significand_bits<double>() - 2);
3062 exponent = (std::numeric_limits<double>::min_exponent - num_significand_bits<double>()) - shift;
3063 significand <<= shift;
3064 }
3065
3066 // Compute the first several nonzero decimal significand digits.
3067 // We call the number we get the first segment.
3068 const int k = info::kappa - dragonbox::floor_log10_pow2(exponent);
3069 exp = -k;
3070 const int beta = exponent + dragonbox::floor_log2_pow10(k);
3071 uint64_t first_segment;
3072 bool has_more_segments;
3073 int digits_in_the_first_segment;
3074 {
3075 const auto r = dragonbox::umul192_upper128(significand << beta, dragonbox::get_cached_power(k));
3076 first_segment = r.high();
3077 has_more_segments = r.low() != 0;
3078
3079 // The first segment can have 18 ~ 19 digits.
3080 if (first_segment >= 1000000000000000000ULL) {
3081 digits_in_the_first_segment = 19;
3082 } else {
3083 // When it is of 18-digits, we align it to 19-digits by adding a bogus
3084 // zero at the end.
3085 digits_in_the_first_segment = 18;
3086 first_segment *= 10;
3087 }
3088 }
3089
3090 // Compute the actual number of decimal digits to print.
3091 if (fixed) adjust_precision(precision, exp + digits_in_the_first_segment);
3092
3093 // Use Dragon4 only when there might be not enough digits in the first
3094 // segment.
3095 if (digits_in_the_first_segment > precision) {
3096 use_dragon = false;
3097
3098 if (precision <= 0) {
3099 exp += digits_in_the_first_segment;
3100
3101 if (precision < 0) {
3102 // Nothing to do, since all we have are just leading zeros.
3103 buf.try_resize(0);
3104 } else {
3105 // We may need to round-up.
3106 buf.try_resize(1);
3107 if ((first_segment | static_cast<uint64_t>(has_more_segments)) > 5000000000000000000ULL) {
3108 buf[0] = '1';
3109 } else {
3110 buf[0] = '0';
3111 }
3112 }
3113 } // precision <= 0
3114 else {
3115 exp += digits_in_the_first_segment - precision;
3116
3117 // When precision > 0, we divide the first segment into three
3118 // subsegments, each with 9, 9, and 0 ~ 1 digits so that each fits
3119 // in 32-bits which usually allows faster calculation than in
3120 // 64-bits. Since some compiler (e.g. MSVC) doesn't know how to optimize
3121 // division-by-constant for large 64-bit divisors, we do it here
3122 // manually. The magic number 7922816251426433760 below is equal to
3123 // ceil(2^(64+32) / 10^10).
3124 const uint32_t first_subsegment =
3125 static_cast<uint32_t>(dragonbox::umul128_upper64(first_segment, 7922816251426433760ULL) >> 32);
3126 const uint64_t second_third_subsegments = first_segment - first_subsegment * 10000000000ULL;
3127
3128 uint64_t prod;
3129 uint32_t digits;
3130 bool should_round_up;
3131 int number_of_digits_to_print = precision > 9 ? 9 : precision;
3132
3133 // Print a 9-digits subsegment, either the first or the second.
3134 auto print_subsegment = [&](uint32_t subsegment, char* buffer) {
3135 int number_of_digits_printed = 0;
3136
3137 // If we want to print an odd number of digits from the subsegment,
3138 if ((number_of_digits_to_print & 1) != 0) {
3139 // Convert to 64-bit fixed-point fractional form with 1-digit
3140 // integer part. The magic number 720575941 is a good enough
3141 // approximation of 2^(32 + 24) / 10^8; see
3142 // https://jk-jeon.github.io/posts/2022/12/fixed-precision-formatting/#fixed-length-case
3143 // for details.
3144 prod = ((subsegment * static_cast<uint64_t>(720575941)) >> 24) + 1;
3145 digits = static_cast<uint32_t>(prod >> 32);
3146 *buffer = static_cast<char>('0' + digits);
3147 number_of_digits_printed++;
3148 }
3149 // If we want to print an even number of digits from the
3150 // first_subsegment,
3151 else {
3152 // Convert to 64-bit fixed-point fractional form with 2-digits
3153 // integer part. The magic number 450359963 is a good enough
3154 // approximation of 2^(32 + 20) / 10^7; see
3155 // https://jk-jeon.github.io/posts/2022/12/fixed-precision-formatting/#fixed-length-case
3156 // for details.
3157 prod = ((subsegment * static_cast<uint64_t>(450359963)) >> 20) + 1;
3158 digits = static_cast<uint32_t>(prod >> 32);
3159 copy2(buffer, digits2(digits));
3160 number_of_digits_printed += 2;
3161 }
3162
3163 // Print all digit pairs.
3164 while (number_of_digits_printed < number_of_digits_to_print) {
3165 prod = static_cast<uint32_t>(prod) * static_cast<uint64_t>(100);
3166 digits = static_cast<uint32_t>(prod >> 32);
3167 copy2(buffer + number_of_digits_printed, digits2(digits));
3168 number_of_digits_printed += 2;
3169 }
3170 };
3171
3172 // Print first subsegment.
3173 print_subsegment(first_subsegment, buf.data());
3174
3175 // Perform rounding if the first subsegment is the last subsegment to
3176 // print.
3177 if (precision <= 9) {
3178 // Rounding inside the subsegment.
3179 // We round-up if:
3180 // - either the fractional part is strictly larger than 1/2, or
3181 // - the fractional part is exactly 1/2 and the last digit is odd.
3182 // We rely on the following observations:
3183 // - If fractional_part >= threshold, then the fractional part is
3184 // strictly larger than 1/2.
3185 // - If the MSB of fractional_part is set, then the fractional part
3186 // must be at least 1/2.
3187 // - When the MSB of fractional_part is set, either
3188 // second_third_subsegments being nonzero or has_more_segments
3189 // being true means there are further digits not printed, so the
3190 // fractional part is strictly larger than 1/2.
3191 if (precision < 9) {
3192 uint32_t fractional_part = static_cast<uint32_t>(prod);
3193 should_round_up =
3194 fractional_part >=
3195 data::fractional_part_rounding_thresholds[8 - number_of_digits_to_print] ||
3196 ((fractional_part >> 31) &
3197 ((digits & 1) | (second_third_subsegments != 0) | has_more_segments)) != 0;
3198 }
3199 // Rounding at the subsegment boundary.
3200 // In this case, the fractional part is at least 1/2 if and only if
3201 // second_third_subsegments >= 5000000000ULL, and is strictly larger
3202 // than 1/2 if we further have either second_third_subsegments >
3203 // 5000000000ULL or has_more_segments == true.
3204 else {
3205 should_round_up =
3206 second_third_subsegments > 5000000000ULL ||
3207 (second_third_subsegments == 5000000000ULL && ((digits & 1) != 0 || has_more_segments));
3208 }
3209 }
3210 // Otherwise, print the second subsegment.
3211 else {
3212 // Compilers are not aware of how to leverage the maximum value of
3213 // second_third_subsegments to find out a better magic number which
3214 // allows us to eliminate an additional shift. 1844674407370955162 =
3215 // ceil(2^64/10) < ceil(2^64*(10^9/(10^10 - 1))).
3216 const uint32_t second_subsegment = static_cast<uint32_t>(
3217 dragonbox::umul128_upper64(second_third_subsegments, 1844674407370955162ULL));
3218 const uint32_t third_subsegment =
3219 static_cast<uint32_t>(second_third_subsegments) - second_subsegment * 10;
3220
3221 number_of_digits_to_print = precision - 9;
3222 print_subsegment(second_subsegment, buf.data() + 9);
3223
3224 // Rounding inside the subsegment.
3225 if (precision < 18) {
3226 // The condition third_subsegment != 0 implies that the segment was
3227 // of 19 digits, so in this case the third segment should be
3228 // consisting of a genuine digit from the input.
3229 uint32_t fractional_part = static_cast<uint32_t>(prod);
3230 should_round_up =
3231 fractional_part >=
3232 data::fractional_part_rounding_thresholds[8 - number_of_digits_to_print] ||
3233 ((fractional_part >> 31) & ((digits & 1) | (third_subsegment != 0) | has_more_segments)) !=
3234 0;
3235 }
3236 // Rounding at the subsegment boundary.
3237 else {
3238 // In this case, the segment must be of 19 digits, thus
3239 // the third subsegment should be consisting of a genuine digit from
3240 // the input.
3241 should_round_up =
3242 third_subsegment > 5 || (third_subsegment == 5 && ((digits & 1) != 0 || has_more_segments));
3243 }
3244 }
3245
3246 // Round-up if necessary.
3247 if (should_round_up) {
3248 ++buf[precision - 1];
3249 for (int i = precision - 1; i > 0 && buf[i] > '9'; --i) {
3250 buf[i] = '0';
3251 ++buf[i - 1];
3252 }
3253 if (buf[0] > '9') {
3254 buf[0] = '1';
3255 if (fixed) buf[precision++] = '0';
3256 else ++exp;
3257 }
3258 }
3259 buf.try_resize(to_unsigned(precision));
3260 }
3261 } // if (digits_in_the_first_segment > precision)
3262 else {
3263 // Adjust the exponent for its use in Dragon4.
3264 exp += digits_in_the_first_segment - 1;
3265 }
3266 }
3267 if (use_dragon) {
3268 auto f = basic_fp<uint128_t>();
3269 bool is_predecessor_closer = specs.binary32 ? f.assign(static_cast<float>(value)) : f.assign(converted_value);
3270 if (is_predecessor_closer) dragon_flags |= dragon::predecessor_closer;
3271 if (fixed) dragon_flags |= dragon::fixed;
3272 // Limit precision to the maximum possible number of significant digits in
3273 // an IEEE754 double because we don't need to generate zeros.
3274 const int max_double_digits = 767;
3275 if (precision > max_double_digits) precision = max_double_digits;
3276 format_dragon(f, dragon_flags, precision, buf, exp);
3277 }
3278 if (!fixed && !specs.showpoint) {
3279 // Remove trailing zeros.
3280 auto num_digits = buf.size();
3281 while (num_digits > 0 && buf[num_digits - 1] == '0') {
3282 --num_digits;
3283 ++exp;
3284 }
3285 buf.try_resize(num_digits);
3286 }
3287 return exp;
3288}
3289
3290template <typename Char, typename OutputIt, typename T>
3291FMT_CONSTEXPR20 auto write_float(OutputIt out, T value, format_specs<Char> specs, locale_ref loc) -> OutputIt {
3292 float_specs fspecs = parse_float_type_spec(specs);
3293 fspecs.sign = specs.sign;
3294 if (detail::signbit(value)) { // value < 0 is false for NaN so use signbit.
3295 fspecs.sign = sign::minus;
3296 value = -value;
3297 } else if (fspecs.sign == sign::minus) {
3298 fspecs.sign = sign::none;
3299 }
3300
3301 if (!detail::isfinite(value)) return write_nonfinite(out, detail::isnan(value), specs, fspecs);
3302
3303 if (specs.align == align::numeric && fspecs.sign) {
3304 auto it = reserve(out, 1);
3305 *it++ = detail::sign<Char>(fspecs.sign);
3306 out = base_iterator(out, it);
3307 fspecs.sign = sign::none;
3308 if (specs.width != 0) --specs.width;
3309 }
3310
3311 memory_buffer buffer;
3312 if (fspecs.format == float_format::hex) {
3313 if (fspecs.sign) buffer.push_back(detail::sign<char>(fspecs.sign));
3314 format_hexfloat(convert_float(value), specs.precision, fspecs, buffer);
3315 return write_bytes<align::right>(out, {buffer.data(), buffer.size()}, specs);
3316 }
3317 int precision = specs.precision >= 0 || specs.type == presentation_type::none ? specs.precision : 6;
3318 if (fspecs.format == float_format::exp) {
3319 if (precision == max_value<int>()) throw_format_error("number is too big");
3320 else ++precision;
3321 } else if (fspecs.format != float_format::fixed && precision == 0) {
3322 precision = 1;
3323 }
3324 if (const_check(std::is_same<T, float>())) fspecs.binary32 = true;
3325 int exp = format_float(convert_float(value), precision, fspecs, buffer);
3326 fspecs.precision = precision;
3327 auto f = big_decimal_fp {buffer.data(), static_cast<int>(buffer.size()), exp};
3328 return write_float(out, f, specs, fspecs, loc);
3329}
3330
3331template <typename Char, typename OutputIt, typename T, FMT_ENABLE_IF(is_floating_point<T>::value)>
3332FMT_CONSTEXPR20 auto write(OutputIt out, T value, format_specs<Char> specs, locale_ref loc = {}) -> OutputIt {
3333 if (const_check(!is_supported_floating_point(value))) return out;
3334 return specs.localized && write_loc(out, value, specs, loc) ? out : write_float(out, value, specs, loc);
3335}
3336
3337template <typename Char, typename OutputIt, typename T, FMT_ENABLE_IF(is_fast_float<T>::value)>
3338FMT_CONSTEXPR20 auto write(OutputIt out, T value) -> OutputIt {
3339 if (is_constant_evaluated()) return write(out, value, format_specs<Char>());
3340 if (const_check(!is_supported_floating_point(value))) return out;
3341
3342 auto fspecs = float_specs();
3343 if (detail::signbit(value)) {
3344 fspecs.sign = sign::minus;
3345 value = -value;
3346 }
3347
3348 constexpr auto specs = format_specs<Char>();
3349 using floaty = conditional_t<std::is_same<T, long double>::value, double, T>;
3350 using floaty_uint = typename dragonbox::float_info<floaty>::carrier_uint;
3351 floaty_uint mask = exponent_mask<floaty>();
3352 if ((bit_cast<floaty_uint>(value) & mask) == mask) return write_nonfinite(out, std::isnan(value), specs, fspecs);
3353
3354 auto dec = dragonbox::to_decimal(static_cast<floaty>(value));
3355 return write_float(out, dec, specs, fspecs, {});
3356}

3519template <template <typename> class Handler, typename FormatArg, typename ErrorHandler>
3520FMT_CONSTEXPR auto get_dynamic_spec(FormatArg arg, ErrorHandler eh) -> int {
3521 unsigned long long value = visit_format_arg(Handler<ErrorHandler>(eh), arg);
3522 if (value > to_unsigned(max_value<int>())) eh.on_error("number is too big");
3523 return static_cast<int>(value);
3524}

3526template <typename Context, typename ID> FMT_CONSTEXPR auto get_arg(Context& ctx, ID id) -> decltype(ctx.arg(id)) {
3527 auto arg = ctx.arg(id);
3528 if (!arg) ctx.on_error("argument not found");
3529 return arg;
3530}
3531
3532template <template <typename> class Handler, typename Context>
3533FMT_CONSTEXPR void handle_dynamic_spec(int& value, arg_ref<typename Context::char_type> ref, Context& ctx) {
3534 switch (ref.kind) {
3535 case arg_id_kind::none: break;
3536 case arg_id_kind::index:
3537 value = detail::get_dynamic_spec<Handler>(get_arg(ctx, ref.val.index), ctx.error_handler());
3538 break;
3539 case arg_id_kind::name:
3540 value = detail::get_dynamic_spec<Handler>(get_arg(ctx, ref.val.name), ctx.error_handler());
3541 break;
3542 }
3543}

3639class format_int {
3640 private:
3641 // Buffer should be large enough to hold all digits (digits10 + 1),
3642 // a sign and a null character.
3643 enum { buffer_size = std::numeric_limits<unsigned long long>::digits10 + 3 };
3644
3645 mutable char buffer_[buffer_size];
3646 char* str_;
3647
3648 template <typename UInt> auto format_unsigned(UInt value) -> char* {
3649 auto n = static_cast<detail::uint32_or_64_or_128_t<UInt>>(value);
3650 return detail::format_decimal(buffer_, n, buffer_size - 1).begin;
3651 }
3652
3653 template <typename Int> auto format_signed(Int value) -> char* {
3654 auto abs_value = static_cast<detail::uint32_or_64_or_128_t<Int>>(value);
3655 bool negative = value < 0;
3656 if (negative) abs_value = 0 - abs_value;
3657 auto begin = format_unsigned(abs_value);
3658 if (negative) *--begin = '-';
3659 return begin;
3660 }
3661 public:
3662 explicit format_int(int value) : str_(format_signed(value)) {}
3663
3664 explicit format_int(long value) : str_(format_signed(value)) {}
3665
3666 explicit format_int(long long value) : str_(format_signed(value)) {}
3667
3668 explicit format_int(unsigned value) : str_(format_unsigned(value)) {}
3669
3670 explicit format_int(unsigned long value) : str_(format_unsigned(value)) {}
3671
3672 explicit format_int(unsigned long long value) : str_(format_unsigned(value)) {}
3673
3675 auto size() const -> size_t { return detail::to_unsigned(buffer_ - str_ + buffer_size - 1); }
3676
3681 auto data() const -> const char* { return str_; }
3682
3687 auto c_str() const -> const char* {
3688 buffer_[buffer_size - 1] = '\0';
3689 return str_;
3690 }
3691
3697 auto str() const -> std::string { return std::string(str_, size()); }
3698};

3868 return value_formatter_.parse(ctx);
3869 }
3870
3871 template <typename FormatContext>
3872 auto format(const join_view<It, Sentinel, Char>& value, FormatContext& ctx) const -> decltype(ctx.out()) {
3873 auto it = value.begin;
3874 auto out = ctx.out();
3875 if (it != value.end) {
3876 out = value_formatter_.format(*it, ctx);
3877 ++it;
3878 while (it != value.end) {
3879 out = detail::copy_str<Char>(value.sep.begin(), value.sep.end(), out);
3880 ctx.advance_to(out);
3881 out = value_formatter_.format(*it, ctx);
3882 ++it;
3883 }
3884 }
3885 return out;
3886 }
3887};

3893template <typename It, typename Sentinel> auto join(It begin, Sentinel end, string_view sep)
3894 -> join_view<It, Sentinel> {
3895 return {begin, end, sep};
3896}

3915 -> join_view<detail::iterator_t<Range>, detail::sentinel_t<Range>> {
3916 return join(std::begin(range), std::end(range), sep);
3917}

3937template <typename T, FMT_ENABLE_IF(std::is_integral<T>::value)> FMT_NODISCARD inline auto to_string(T value)
3938 -> std::string {
3939 // The buffer should be large enough to store the number including the sign
3940 // or "false" for bool.

3942 char buffer[max_size > 5 ? static_cast<unsigned>(max_size) : 5];
3943 char* begin = buffer;
3944 return std::string(begin, detail::write<char>(begin, value));
3945}

3963template <typename Char> void vformat_to(buffer<Char>& buf, basic_string_view<Char> fmt,
3964 typename vformat_args<Char>::type args, locale_ref loc) {
3965 auto out = buffer_appender<Char>(buf);
3966 if (fmt.size() == 2 && equal2(fmt.data(), "{}")) {
3967 auto arg = args.get(0);
3968 if (!arg) error_handler().on_error("argument not found");
3969 visit_format_arg(default_arg_formatter<Char> {out, args, loc}, arg);
3970 return;
3971 }
3972
3973 struct format_handler : error_handler {
3974 basic_format_parse_context<Char> parse_context;
3975 buffer_context<Char> context;
3976
3977 format_handler(buffer_appender<Char> p_out, basic_string_view<Char> str,
3978 basic_format_args<buffer_context<Char>> p_args, locale_ref p_loc)
3979 : parse_context(str), context(p_out, p_args, p_loc) {}
3980
3981 void on_text(const Char* begin, const Char* end) {
3982 auto text = basic_string_view<Char>(begin, to_unsigned(end - begin));
3983 context.advance_to(write<Char>(context.out(), text));
3984 }
3985
3986 FMT_CONSTEXPR auto on_arg_id() -> int { return parse_context.next_arg_id(); }
3987
3988 FMT_CONSTEXPR auto on_arg_id(int id) -> int { return parse_context.check_arg_id(id), id; }
3989
3990 FMT_CONSTEXPR auto on_arg_id(basic_string_view<Char> id) -> int {
3991 int arg_id = context.arg_id(id);
3992 if (arg_id < 0) on_error("argument not found");
3993 return arg_id;
3994 }
3995
3996 FMT_INLINE void on_replacement_field(int id, const Char*) {
3997 auto arg = get_arg(context, id);
3998 context.advance_to(visit_format_arg(
3999 default_arg_formatter<Char> {context.out(), context.args(), context.locale()}, arg));
4000 }
4001
4002 auto on_format_specs(int id, const Char* begin, const Char* end) -> const Char* {
4003 auto arg = get_arg(context, id);
4004 if (arg.type() == type::custom_type) {
4005 parse_context.advance_to(begin);
4006 visit_format_arg(custom_formatter<Char> {parse_context, context}, arg);
4007 return parse_context.begin();
4008 }
4009 auto specs = detail::dynamic_format_specs<Char>();
4010 begin = parse_format_specs(begin, end, specs, parse_context, arg.type());
4011 detail::handle_dynamic_spec<detail::width_checker>(specs.width, specs.width_ref, context);
4012 detail::handle_dynamic_spec<detail::precision_checker>(specs.precision, specs.precision_ref, context);
4013 if (begin == end || *begin != '}') on_error("missing '}' in format string");
4014 auto f = arg_formatter<Char> {context.out(), specs, context.locale()};
4015 context.advance_to(visit_format_arg(f, arg));
4016 return begin;
4017 }
4018 };
4019
4020 detail::parse_format_string<false>(fmt, format_handler(out, fmt, args, loc));
4021}
